        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 1:49PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 149 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Missouri City, or near Buckner, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Independence, Buckner, Orrick, Sibley, Missouri City, and Levasy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
